{"hash":"0e247e0a69d12fb61a69a6933cca118d0afd045f","data":{"post":{"id":"eb211b783fad7a97b4f1c3e873ef5d2c","title":"Creating a \"Swipe-to-Confirm\" Component","content":"<blockquote>\n<p>The Amazon app features a Slide-to-Confirm element inspired by Apple's \"Swipe to Unlock\". Surprisingly, a similar component is nowhere on the internet, so I'll need to create it myself.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Designers can use Slide-to-Confirm as a tool to help their users feel more secure (than a button that can be accidentally tapped) and more accomplished (takes more work to slide across the screen). Amazon uses it in their \"Buy Now\" flow to prevent accidental purchases. </p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 381 825' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-60a258ffd78cc4427c2aed59fb282a51'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-60a258ffd78cc4427c2aed59fb282a51)' width='381' height='825' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAACLCAYAAADRRp%2bpAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEwEAmpwYAAAgAElEQVR42uV9B3hVZbZ2/nvnv3Pv3DLj6NxxlF7SSCO9V0hCCISE9IT0hDRCIAmBAKFXC4MVe0WlK5ZrBxvWAStiRZQiTXpP8v7r/fb5TvY5OQFUrsz84rPc%2b%2bz2rfWud5Xv2xt1cvaOhLNXBLgdqLbhIhGyH6nEOG4rtucjrNddPtH6RKh9q8gxF88oOHtadPUS27zC1HagxW4nZaDl4oEWEIyHRSkZoA31iTaBFGkdRIPwSxutDRjobTbc7KQoy7WGQ118BIzBYoNPlHGvxW4ns1H6QQMFoQGeYSKh6nd/j1D0GOiHPm4B8qBwE0iXlwFWECz69/cQnT3ClfQfZOz3k%2b1Ajwhc298Pf%2bnro%2bygbQMt4DmZQ6CvWzCiE9JRM3EqUjKL0NAyB82tCzE8LR8lVRMxe/HN6K1AuPwAdDU%2bFD7B8QgIH4bQmJGIG56FrIIaZIypRlBkIu59eAWeef5l3LLsfoTFpliZ42SmMJHxDIzD2PFTED8iC5Wynb1oKdJzy1A8doIcb8G1A/zhOjjKAtp5QkAD5GUOqwgL8hGO983HbI5H2oyljysdhNJ9xHE5xbVYuGQZ4oZlIDo%2bTfRtRHpeBWoaWsXgkXhh4%2bv4/IuvsO6J5%2bR8ptynQ8CiZGciiYLb4Bi4yG83iRnfsAR1rrdrEPq6B8M%2bZDpzgslwb3vDNRgW0LztQLEBxPJ8r04PdwUgshMA5bhw5X3fk