.png\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/writing/assets/static/amazon2.6031c4f.cda009aaee987c144bafa562be35826f.png\" width=\"381\" alt=\"final\"></noscript>\n<img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 739 1600' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-382d6b0dfc2a5ac51da3c010eda2d527'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-382d6b0dfc2a5ac51da3c010eda2d527)' width='739' height='1600' xlink:href='data:image/jpeg%3bbase64%%2bh%2bVSb5eDKwu2TYMYgjEQo79bziFNEdMoAkH5mt9pbpZtbxt/D7tS3JDZ3YMCDGp5EEgkjnEdawWArCw05hrnGpGQOhMJiZBI6qiRPy60sUOk25WuQG/NMmpiHG7UJSq5tmfiCjGvrVe2gxPdNcLaOw%%2btYYdsiCpJuriU9UtiJ8zV1tmENNIbbSEoQAlKRyAoSMWu2UbbfCFC9axNBUUZNy4mdAehiqq4muw3lq3cW62XkBTaxCgetUu/2SIUTbXPs9A4P%2bRRokotu0c/xF0tJSlEF1w5UA9%2b/lT3Ze0DNi67BKnF%2b8rmY/7qT9j18fxF1dJKQjKlKE8u%2bp76U3WyhhlLTSQltAgCiLGNGp1q8cUxwb6WkhX3kpmU%%2bdM2dk9qkhP7moRMy1z7df/TXaGsQui8pDjNqgBehFwCVJkTp3jMfKsWL6/U%2bEusWaG95lJ4gTl11jv7unie1Qpxh3ZTataDms1T0KWvqah/Y/anMd9hrriY0yNwZ9a7o3iF6VOh21tkJSCULFyCFajSI0%2btet3mILuinh7UM72Enf%2b0UT70Dr4UB8/wBxsVtKqcuDXZ8h9a8xbZra%2b%%2b0zSMpyHQeNc9vh10%2bklm0W2vMbp9YzTCjpHapc0CYE8%2btFaMBNE0UUAUVCuAC%2bqR0Fa8o7CsuRhyGNFJ7t1bKUqatV3EnUIIBA76860casKIOHXYMSPZSZ8OfP6Vn2IjyJD%2bikCrx0IzJwy7UYJywif91S2jvGgpTSmyR7qwJHpT2BZLGlFcpucQvW71pptu5caWTmdS7Ab16irpsq4tbbedaleweZJ618jh%2bZXKyrHpX6fRzcP1R2seuMJWsqJUCexrHhkfEv1rfRX2qR4aRo4ZHxL9aOGR8S/WouNYJh%2bNtNNYpb79Das6BnUmDEfhIpR9gdmv4b/AD3f6qaoaosPDI%2bJfrRwyD%2bJfrVe%2bwOzX8N/nu/1U3wXBMPwRlxrDLfcNuKzqGdSpMR%2bImmqGqNB2cw4mS0qf85qdZWFvZgBhJSAI1JNSqK8%2bPh4MUtoQSfxHWWWclUmz//Z' /%3e%3c/svg%3e\" width=\"739\" alt=\"final\" data-srcset=\"/writing/assets/static/amazon3.c484d7f.c7da86516c6f6515d2f0be6499fecc0b.jpeg 739w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 739px) 100vw, 739px\" data-src=\"/writing/assets/static/amazon3.c484d7f.c7da86516c6f6515d2f0be6499fecc0b.jpeg\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/writing/assets/static/amazon3.c484d7f.c7da86516c6f6515d2f0be6499fecc0b.jpeg\" width=\"739\" alt=\"final\"></noscript></p>\n<p>The UX of this component is great! Showing green and changing the message as you swipe brings out the security and accomplishment feelings. Unfortunately, it's also highly custom.</p>\n<h3 id=\"looking-for-similars-online\"><a href=\"#looking-for-similars-online\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Looking for similar's online</h3>\n<p>The only similar Javascript-based components I could find online were this <a href=\"https://codepen.io/bennettfeely/pen/jyGeJ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">codepen</a>, this <a href=\"https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2011/implementing-iphones-slider-unlock-with-input-typerange/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">blog</a>, and this <a href=\"https://github.com/agentS/react-native-slider-button\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">React Native library</a>; none of which really come close to the functionality I'm looking for. Android and iOS devs had something closer but I'm looking for a Javascript and CSS solution. They all use the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;input type=&#39;range&#39;</code> element, so let's start with that.</p>\n<h3 id=\"browser-support-for-thumb-range\"><a href=\"#browser-support-for-thumb-range\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Browser support for Thumb Range</h3>\n<p>Using the blog to help kickstart my progress, I made a codepen and quickly figured out some interesting things. The blog only supports Firefox when applying CSS to the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;input type=&#39;range&#39;</code> element using <code class=\"language-text\">input::-moz-range-thumb</code>. I needed to include <code class=\"language-text\">input::-webkit-slider-thumb</code> for support on Safari and Chrome, the platforms I'm developing for.</p>\n<p>Also strange is that Chrome required a <code class=\"language-text\">margin-bottom: -7px</code> in order to center the slider vertically.</p>\n<p>Progress on the component here:\n<a href=\"https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/dyyJMKO\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/dyyJMKO</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"a-new-idea\"><a href=\"#a-new-idea\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>A new idea</h3>\n<p>Turning my attention to how I'll solve changing the track message and colour as you swipe got me looking at something new: draggable components. </p>\n<p>What if I was able to use some drag-and-drop JavaScript to make my slider?</p>\n<p>Staring with <a href=\"https://www.kirupa.com/html5/drag.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this drag tutorial from Kirupa</a>, I first modified it to only drag horizontally and then to not drag over the container width.</p>\n<p>Progress here:\n<a href=\"https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/GRRyjzZ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/GRRyjzZ</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"is-the-new-idea-feasable\"><a href=\"#is-the-new-idea-feasable\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Is the new idea feasable?</h3>\n<p>If the new idea could actually work, then I'll be able to put elements on both sides of the slide item that will show and hide as I move the slide item. </p>\n<p>I was able to create this functionality with blue and green bars. The most difficult part about this was honestly figuring out the logic of the HTML elements. I decided that having two tracks on top of each other with <code class=\"language-text\">position: absolute</code> and a high <code class=\"language-text\">z-index</code> for the item worked best: </p>\n<div class=\"gridsome-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>outerContainer<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>container<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>item<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>container<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>green<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>blue<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The bars move by changing their width in JS along with the drag of the item.</p>\n<p>Progress here:\n<a href=\"https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/rNNpWdX\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/rNNpWdX</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"text-in-the-bars\"><a href=\"#text-in-the-bars\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Text in the Bars</h3>\n<p>Now to have text within the bars so that sliding reveals/conseals the text. I quickly made an inner div with the text and made it fit to the grandparent: </p>\n<div class=\"gridsome-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">#bar_inner</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  // center the text\n  <span class=\"token property\">height</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 100%<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> flex<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">justify-content</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> center<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">align-items</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> center<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  \n  // position bar\n  <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 100%<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">position</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> absolute<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">left</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>However this made both text's appear on top of each other. </p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 2354 268' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-d3fdec60a702dfb3dc0c1cde06456aa9'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-d3fdec60a702dfb3dc0c1cde06456aa9)' width='2354' height='268' xlink:href='data:image/png%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAHCAYAAAC4NEsKAAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAACPElEQVQ4y72UTWsTURSG8wdc1FpR27ULF2XECCXRTNq0BkrTtKkrJUm/XFTRxmhNFyJ%2btIkGQxWpHwjGTVUQoeAmXagbxUJcCKINxNYkM5PJtJPU0oiCwuuZm1ijq8SaLh7uWdyZuec57x2dNXsdNZmTqJdHUbfsAffyDlraFRz1Pkf43k3cJ455X8DUIaGlSyBSaLYLxbo8mu2ptbUcSp%2bpBq0OAXtbkwhN5qDbr17F5owXO2Qftq0Mo2HmFi6cn4a60I/vi06GVl8cfwJjewaW7iSTUOlHSxv6s%2bFkkY0RoL23jQToLQn4J7LQ8WqICajP%2bLAldwrc7GXEZr34seTGqjiIVeEI1b34EPXAfvg9TLZ0xQJ%2bN6U1mqBaS5NIMtOEzCjslao%2b/V8J0AQErjEBhQQ0ZM6gZmkEltgolLkhfJX7kZcG8IUxSCkYQO/Qa0qBUkxBhQKoWaM1Cs4whd37HqOxKUz1Q%2bwxTbOVMzyAnn9KVy3G5FT7CqwJMFMCapkAH%2bqyp6GP%2bjH/xsOmnqcE5EUtAX2Ivz2BHtc78DZtav96OEpA5zzMtjj4jrkCthjD3BknPrI91Zy%2bRltP4R/ABBjUIDbJw9gqj6D283Fsj0wiMPYIuU8ufJOdlAQnqwNXptBkTdNhkzSl1DoQ6BqJhFRELFnFdb67PLR0cXwCYyEVOkfuNnYunkOjcgm7Vs7C%2bCoMxyEF48EInkUmGP7gDLqcaXS7JDjc/wnXX7g3joN9Eg5QCm7cXcZPncVppjVW6yMAAAAASUVORK5CYII=' /%3e%3c/svg%3e\" width=\"2354\" alt=\"brokentext\" data-srcset=\"/writing/assets/static/brokentext.82a2fbd.f29109f5483ba0ac80e931f5a4a86025.png 480w, /writing/assets/static/brokentext.cbab2cf.f29109f5483ba0ac80e931f5a4a86025.png 1024w, /writing/assets/static/brokentext.2665e34.f29109f5483ba0ac80e931f5a4a86025.png 1920w, /writing/assets/static/brokentext.01a59f3.f29109f5483ba0ac80e931f5a4a86025.png 2354w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 2354px) 100vw, 2354px\" data-src=\"/writing/assets/static/brokentext.01a59f3.f29109f5483ba0ac80e931f5a4a86025.png\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/writing/assets/static/brokentext.01a59f3.f29109f5483ba0ac80e931f5a4a86025.png\" width=\"2354\" alt=\"brokentext\"></noscript></p>\n<p>And adding  <code class=\"language-text\">overflow: hidden</code> to the parent bar's does nothing (because the parent is not absolute as well). I'm actually really stuck here... 🤔</p>\n<p>In the end I went with not the most elegant solution, but I think with a CSS transition it can be okay. I used JS to switch the <code class=\"language-text\">z-index</code> of the bars, so that the text essentially switches places and is covered by the other bar. </p>\n<p>See it here:\n<a href=\"https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/poopRzX\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/poopRzX</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"confirm-alert-and-fallback\"><a href=\"#confirm-alert-and-fallback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Confirm alert, and fallback</h3>\n<p>Now that I have my meat set up, I need to add the potatoes. I need to trigger an event once the slider reaches the end and if the slider doesn't reach the end, it should fallback to the beginning. </p>\n<p>Both potatoes were pretty easy, just needed to have some logic in the <code class=\"language-text\">dragEnd</code> function</p>\n<div class=\"gridsome-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// in dragEnd(e)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>currentX <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span> dragWidth<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">setTranslate</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> dragItem<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Confirmed!\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>I've added an animation on fallback and wrapped the alert in a function for the CodePen:\n<a href=\"https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/BaaJYbx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/BaaJYbx</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"finalizing\"><a href=\"#finalizing\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Finalizing</h3>\n<p>To finish it off, I cleaned up my code using BEM CSS, and removed some of the unnecessary things like the coloured bars(*) and styled the dragItem. </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>(*) Since the <code class=\"language-text\">overflow: hidden</code> didn't work, it's better to go with an opacity change for the text and changing the background colour of the bar instead of keeping two different ones. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/QWWamxW\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/QWWamxW</a></p>\n<p><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill='none' viewBox='0 0 1372 302' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id='__svg-blur-a53798a0b9b624333a03061b4933773c'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in='SourceGraphic' stdDeviation='40'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x='0' y='0' filter='url(%23__svg-blur-a53798a0b9b624333a03061b4933773c)' width='1372' height='302' xlink:href='data:image/gif%3bbase64%2ciVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAEAAAAAOCAYAAACfOxrCAAAACXBIWXMAAAPoAAAD6AG1e1JrAAADZklEQVRIx9WW2U8TURTG%2b3cYl4T4woMQhHamUwRsBeKLS0hwQ1BRHlABMQqKQtQYUDA8%2bqLR8OATRoK7iMEFt8SYKAKCUZZ2FjrFArZlUT7PvdNWgxFwA/vwy7l37pm5Pd8995yadM8EOt760dvrRk%2bPh9BnTXvnKKezy0f4p8E3xf4rZv/99k4fNC0A07mLMs5UVqDlahaarmTjboiGn1iC%2bTU3ZOHMqRokpffB6lAhrVIiBluqgoQkBbv2qDDdvt6Ily2J8DstGO4hes0Y6WVjcxg2H%2bHPzYYP97Pg1cNUbMluRoz0EcJKJ8wpMscStP/rWFgpI86mICPLCdP9u/XoeGzDqCxSYCIFaVi/0xj7%2bkUMfRD4OMQQXxfQ9cyObbk3EWvzUhY46cNKRCDaFSxfoWBDjgumlqbLeNNKArgECpQFL8DXJ8LVZuaBa50WjClWeN8zEQS%2bzvx8/QLePnUgZ8ctxEokgH1mAczJxuYMqyP4PDgWHd/W5kSARAWZIQHaWyXKAIGfLAt00i3hSl00yvYvQfnBJXh0IwbwSGERwgJQBsxWAEuKgsQ0trGMGCshynQKMp8vE415rGSsJSTJcy2ALSwAO2EvnfykLuFszVIU5y9CXs4CPGuKxbhq5VnxKwKwzeJsMm2moqhExaYdKnbtpQK0V0PZ8QEUH3Yhr0BD/j4NW/NU5FJhyiscgGW%2bMoAJwPDT3a85FoX9%2bYuxO3ch2lrjMCb/pgB0yhlZCgmg4cARDUdPkBilGkrKdZrLKCRhSis0nKzWcLqWxCge4NdlXjIgdAXqL0SjmgSoKo/C64dxgP7nV4C1HzZOSFZ4%2brNUZ%2b0ofoUcnCu8SrMfyPznTABWBAMuMVgERR7k4DsBAaeVz0flUBEU/6wIpswcmCXl3wb/gwAPmqkNPrFRpTcC/NQnEEb7Y0Kw8XDQhmB%2bAeoa3c/t2L7TaIOSw8UrOq/i9m8V/W8izGBn%2bw7rOvHUBjduIwGuNV7H8ztJdMIi9C4Bnm4DfYr9npDfi3vpyNzcQlV8kO6sE/GU0pFAQjJ1HKuC9Zvpj1DdJQ3VlbVoaijAjfoizs1pCPtcLkB11XmkrVWRukY1bISQvk5F8moVxYcGYAoEvkDVJuH1%2bn4RPxQNcOufoXvGIw63exx%2b/wS%2bAn1NdW3iN8IxAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC' /%3e%3c/svg%3e\" width=\"1372\" alt=\"final\" data-srcset=\"/writing/assets/static/final.82a2fbd.6e883588bad609a43065f7294e5e56ab.gif 480w, /writing/assets/static/final.cbab2cf.6e883588bad609a43065f7294e5e56ab.gif 1024w, /writing/assets/static/final.8e3a09a.6e883588bad609a43065f7294e5e56ab.gif 1372w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1372px) 100vw, 1372px\" data-src=\"/writing/assets/static/final.8e3a09a.6e883588bad609a43065f7294e5e56ab.gif\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/writing/assets/static/final.8e3a09a.6e883588bad609a43065f7294e5e56ab.gif\" width=\"1372\" alt=\"final\"></noscript></p>\n<h3 id=\"converting-to-angular\"><a href=\"#converting-to-angular\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Converting to Angular</h3>\n<p>Now that I have the component in JS, I need it in Angular. This was simple enough overall, but had an annoying time making it work due to some scope bugs. After taking the weekend off and then running the code locally, I was able to figure them all out and have it all working. </p>\n<p>I put the final version in CodePen here:\n<a href=\"https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/xxxpzPx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://codepen.io/arjunkalburgi/pen/xxxpzPx</a></p>\n<p>I'd like to go a step further and create a github repo and NPM library for this component, but maybe that'll be for another day! </p>\n<p>Thanks for reading! </p>\n","date":"November 5, 2019","timeToRead":4,"description":"The Amazon app features a Slide-to-Confirm element inspired by Apple's \"Swipe to Unlock\". Surprisingly, a similar component is nowhere on the internet, so I'll need to create it myself.","cover":"/home/runner/work/writing/writing/content/posts/creating-a-slide-to-confirm-component/final.gif"}},"context":{}}